  "prompt": "How much sugar is good for health?",
  "response": "The consumption of sugar should be moderated to maintain good health. The American Heart Association (AHA) recommends the following guidelines for added sugar intake:\n\n- For men: No more than 9 teaspoons (36 grams, or about 150 calories) of added sugar per day.\n- For women: No more than 6 teaspoons (25 grams, or about 100 calories) of added sugar per day.\n\nAdded sugars are those that are added to foods during processing or preparation, as opposed to sugars that naturally occur in fruits, vegetables, and dairy products. Overconsumption of added sugars can lead to various health issues, including obesity, type 2 diabetes, heart disease, and dental problems.\n\nIt's important to read food labels and be mindful of the amount of added sugar in your diet to maintain optimal health. Natural sugars found in whole foods like fruits and vegetables are generally considered healthier because these foods also provide essential nutrients and fiber.",
